          "params": [],
          "returnType": null,
          "description": "Minimum warm-up (ms) before the first beat may be emitted. Default 400. The detector starts hunting a tempo once this much analysis history exists instead of waiting a full slowest-tempo period, so early BeatInfo beats (tagged status: 'provisional') arrive with low latency for visual reactivity. A beat is promoted to status: 'locked' only once the tempo grid is trustworthy (full analysis window + sustained on-grid tracking). Replaces the former settlingMs (default 1500)."
